snippet.textDisplay:
Never forget that the entire concept of FFP is BS. It was an invention of the biggest 10 clubs in Europe. A concept designed to ensure that they would stay at the top forever, barring horrible mismanagement. By making it impossible for teams lower in the leagues or in the lower divisions to spend their way to the top and CHALLENGE them! It builds in a permanent financial advantage to the biggest and most historic clubs, the ones the earn the most. By capping everyone to their revenue.

LIV were able to rise ONLY because they used to be great and built a worldwide fan base through the 70's and 80's. This provided them with TV and merch revenue not available to other mid table teams. They used that revenue wisely to modernize ANfield and further increase revenue. They then further used that additional revenue wisely to acquire high value \ return players. They then sold on several of those players ( Suarez, Sterling, and Coutinho ) for huge profits and then re-invested that revenue wisely yet again on WC players to address specific holes ( VVD, Keita, and Ali). All of which has won them a new generation of fans worldwide along with titles, resulting in yet even more revenue which undoubtedly will adequately the next gen rebuild over the next 2-3 years.
